knowledge_graph.title: Batman Begins
knowledge_graph.description: A young Bruce Wayne (Christian Bale) travels to the Far East, where he's trained in the martial arts by Henri Ducard (Liam Neeson), a member of the mysterious League of Shadows. When Ducard reveals the League's true purpose -- the complete destruction of Gotham City -- Wayne returns to Gotham intent on cleaning up the city without resorting to murder. With the help of Alfred (Michael Caine), his loyal butler, and Lucius Fox (Morgan Freeman), a tech expert at Wayne Enterprises, Batman is born.… MORE

related_questions.question: Why Katie Holmes was replaced in Batman?
related_questions.snippet: Katie Holmes had nothing against Rachel Dawes or Nolan's Batman trilogy; she simply had the desire to explore other roles at the time. In fact, instead of returning as Rachel Dawes for The Dark Knight, she appeared as Jackie Truman in Mad Money.
related_questions.title: The Reason Behind Why Katie Holmes Left The Dark Knight Trilogy

related_questions.question: Is Batman Begins as good as The Dark Knight?
related_questions.snippet: There is no denying that The Dark Knight is nothing short of a masterpiece, and will forever be known as such. Batman Begins may not be the better movie as a whole from a cinematic standpoint, but it may be the better Batman movie. Everything that makes the character who he is gets shown here and built upon.
related_questions.title: Is Batman Begins Actually Better Than The Dark Knight? - MovieWeb

related_questions.question: Should I watch Batman Begins before Dark Knight?
related_questions.snippet: Yes, you can watch "The Dark Knight" without having watched its prequel, "Batman Begins." While "The Dark Knight" is the second film in Christopher Nolan's Batman trilogy, it can be enjoyed as a standalone movie because it has its own storyline and plot.
related_questions.title: Can I watch 'The Dark Knight' without watching its prequel? - Quora

related_questions.question: How old was Cillian Murphy in Batman Begins?
related_questions.snippet: Cillian Murphy was approximately 28 years old when he played Scarecrow in Batman Begins. The film was released in 2005, which means the actor would have filmed it when he was around 26 or 27.
